Message: Hi, I’m the NewsBreak Ad Assistant. How can I help?
The user completes the submission of the form
Hi how to add more people to the account?

To add more people to your account, follow these steps:

1. Access Account Management.
2. Click ‘Access’ under your preferred Organization or Ad account.
3. Select ‘Add User’ on the right-hand side of your screen.
4. Fill in the email address of the new user and their role (Admin, Operator, or Viewer) and submit.

Once submitted, the new user will be prompted to make an account via their email. After email verification, they will see your Organization or Ad account listed under their own Account Management tab.
There is no such button as access

It sounds like you might be in the wrong section or there could be a display issue. Make sure you're in the 'Account Management' section of your Ad Manager. If you're still having trouble, try refreshing the page or clearing your browser cache. If the problem persists, please let me know!
Im in th e account management,  I can see the name of organizations and ad accounts but there is no buttons like add someone

It seems like there might be a permissions issue. To add users, you need to have admin access to the organization or ad account. If you don't have admin access, you won't see the option to add users. You might want to check with someone who has admin rights in your organization to grant you the necessary permissions.
